<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Cameron, Duncan. A Sketch of the Nipigon Country with extracts from His Journal, 1804. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0025</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">2<sup>nd</sup> September, Continued</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> now spoke like a Chief, and as he was One of them <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> for a House here, that I Exspected, that he would encourage his young men to pay their Credits, and not intice any other Indians to go with him to Osnaburgh, in that Case I should Use him like a Chief, and Cloath him as such on my way Out next Spring<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey then all began to make many promises of behaving well<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>his was Just what I wanted, for I was determin'd from the beginning to leave a Canoe here, and Only wanted to be inticed by them, that I might have the more hold Upon them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I then told them that I would leave a Canoe, Especially as the Cotton Shirt, and them that Came with me, desired it, and gave them the 4 two gallon Kegs, desiring them to drink quietly, and not to Come and trouble me, while they were drunk, as I would be very Busy, as soon as my Canoes would arrive, in makeing the Outfit for this place<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey then went to their Loges, with their Liquor &amp; Tobacco, you may sure, and begun their frolic<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span>n the Evening my Canoes <span class="AddHand-editors">[arr]</span>ived<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I would not have Enlarged so much on this Subject, which will undoubtedly appear Nonsentical to the reader, <span class="AddHand-editors">[for any]</span> other reason, than with a view to give them an Idea of <span class="AddHand-editors">[the]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[man]</span>ner in which the Business of this Country is Carried on<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[61]</span></p>

